{"link_name": "Simple Docker Stats monitoring plugin for Zabbix with Discovery", "type": "Template", "OS": "", "vendor": "Others", "minZabbVer": "4.4.x", "link_desc": "<h1 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.25; padding-bottom: 0.3em; border-bottom: 1px solid #eaecef; color: #24292e; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji'; margin: 0px !important 0px 16px 0px;\">Simple Docker Stats monitoring plugin for Zabbix with Discovery</h1>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400;\">This Zabbix plugin can monitoring your Docker containers via Docker Stats. It is a very simple solution for mixed servers where not only containers run (so running native agent).</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400;\">It use discovery so your life will easy with this plugin.</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.5em; line-height: 1.25; padding-bottom: 0.3em; border-bottom: 1px solid #eaecef; color: #24292e; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji';\"><a id=\"user-content-install\" class=\"anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: initial; color: #0366d6; float: left; padding-right: 4px; margin-left: -20px; line-height: 1;\" href=\"https://github.com/dacrhu/zabbix_plugins/tree/master/zbx_docker_stats#install\"></a>Install:</h2>\n<ol style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 2em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Import zbx_template_docker_stats.xml in Zabbix webconsole.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Copy userparameter_docker.conf to Zabbix agent folder of target server.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Restart agent.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">You must set sudo (example: zabbix ALL=NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/docker).</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Add template to target server in Zabbix webconsole.</li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400;\">That is all.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 600;\">Note:</span> tested in version 4.4 but I think it can run with early versions too.</p>\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: -5px; top: -19px;\"> </div>", "features": "Zabbix Agent", "address": "", "city": "", "state": "", "country": "", "postcode": "", "telephone": "", "fax": "", "email": "", "website": "https://github.com/dacrhu/zabbix_plugins/tree/master/zbx_docker_stats", "price": 0, "link_hits": 2470, "link_votes": null, "link_rating": 0, "link_featured": null, "link_created": "2020-02-16 19:17:17", "link_modified": "2020-02-16 19:19:21", "link_visited": 802, "publish_up": "2020-02-16 19:17:17", "publish_down": "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "metakey": "", "metadesc": "", "1.8": "", "2.0": "", "2.2": "", "2.4": "", "3.0": "", "3.2": "", "3.4": "", "4.0": "", "4.2": "", "4.4": "", "5.0": "", "5.2": "", "tags": "docker, stats, simple", "author": "David Horvath", "user_id": 11392, "link_id": 1969, "cat_id": "251", "internal_notes": "", "lat": 0, "lng": 0, "zoom": ""}